The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, December 30, 2003 				 Govt dithers on TV box
																								New Delhi, Dec. 29: The Union information and broadcasting ministry is still unsure on whether it will insist on a rollout of the set-top box regime, despite being armed with a court order, reports our special correspondent. 																								The government continues to be nervous about trouble brewing in its backyard right here in south Delhi that is the testing ground for the conditional access system.																								BJP parliamentary party spokesperson and MP from south Delhi, Vijay Kumar Malhotra, has written to the ministry to reconsider the Cable Television Networks Amendment Act that has enabled CAS. He has also asked if CAS should not be deferred by a year to make the law more consumer-friendly. 
